Within the shrine grounds, stone-carved figures of monkeys—linking the character "申" in "Koushin" with the "猿" (monkey) of {{ill|Sarutahiko Ōkami|ja|猿田彦大神|qq=draft}}—are believed to represent the "Mitsushi" (three corpses) theory of {{ill|Koushin faith|ja|庚申信仰|qq=draft}}, such as the "see no evil, hear no evil, speak no evil" concept, with several hundred carved "saru" present.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|qq=draft}}}}
