'''Koushinsha''' (こうしんしゃ) is a shrine located in [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]], [[:en:Nōgata, Fukuoka|Nogata City]], in the Yamabe area<ref>もと[[:en:Kurate District, Fukuoka|Kurate District]] {{ill|Yamabe Village|ja|山部村 (福岡県)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamabe Village|qq=}}</ref>. It is a shrine that enshrines deities in a [[Shinbutsu-shūgō]] tradition.

Within the shrine grounds, stone-carved figures of monkeys—linking the character "申" in "Koushin" with the "猿" (monkey) of {{ill|Sarutahiko Ōkami|ja|猿田彦大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sarutahiko Ōkami|qq=}}—are believed to represent the "Mitsushi" (three corpses) theory of [[:en:Kōshin|Koushin faith]], such as the "see no evil, hear no evil, speak no evil" concept, with several hundred carved "saru" present.

== Worshipped Deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saijin|qq=}}}}
* In [[:en:Shinto|Shinto]], the deity is {{ill|Sarutahiko Ōkami|ja|猿田彦大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sarutahiko Ōkami|qq=}}.
* In [[:en:Buddhism|Buddhism]], the deity is {{ill|Seimen Kongō|ja|青面金剛|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seimen Kongō|qq=}}.

== History (Yūshi) ==
With {{ill|Sarutahiko Ōkami|ja|猿田彦大神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sarutahiko Ōkami|qq=}} as the principal deity, the shrine was transferred to its present location from the Koushin Shrine in [[:en:Karatsu, Saga|Karatsu]] in February of Genbun 2 (1737).

== Festivals and Events ==
[[File:Koushin002.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Three monkeys]]
* December 5: Annual Grand Festival
* August 5: Natsugoe Festival
* Every month on the 5th: A monthly festival is held (since 1959, a large sale event called "Itsukaichi" has been organized in the central shopping district of Nogata, capitalizing on the divine virtues).

== Location and Transportation ==
: [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]] Nogata City, Yamabe 601
* A 10‑minute walk from [[:en:Nōgata Station|JR Nogata Station]].

